<!-- ============================================================
VOICING PLAN:
- Bb major: I=Bb, ii=Cm, iii=Dm, IV=Eb, V=F, vi=Gm, vii°=A°.
- Non-diatonic: D major → Dm (iii). Cm7 is diatonic ii7.
- Phrase 1 (mm.1-4): Lighter opening — half-note block chords
  with broken inner-voice motion in RH. LH "33" (Bb2-F3-Bb3).
  Mix of root-pos and 1st-inv in LH for variety.
- Phrase 2 (mm.5-8): Same material, fuller. RH rises to broken
  arpeggio in m.5 (Bb3-D4-F4-Bb4). LH adds 4th note in strong
  measures. m.6 uses "334" (triad+octave Bb3→F4→Bb4→D5 range).
- Phrase 3 (mm.9-12): Bridge. Dm (iii) adds new color (mm.9-10).
  Melodic peak at D5. m.11 climax with IV→V→I all quarter notes,
  full 3-note RH + 4-note LH throughout. m.12 final ii-V-I with
  classic 4-3 suspension (C5→Bb4) in both melody and RH.

VOICE LEADING HIGHLIGHTS:
- m.3 passing notes Ab4 G4 in melody (key-sig A natural, but these
  are natural passing tones in Bb major). LH follows with F→Bb→V.
- mm.9-10 (Dm area): A natural appears in melody and RH (A=7th
  degree of Bb major, perfectly diatonic). LH uses D2-A2 open P5.
- m.12 suspension: RH C5→C5→Bb4 is a 4-3 suspension resolving on
  the I chord. LH bass walks C2→F2→Bb2 (P5-P5 down).

TEXTURE ARC:
- mm.1-4: Light, half-note motion (2+3 notes). Refined opening.
- mm.5-8: Building, broken arpeggios and 3-note voicings (2-3+3-4).
- mm.9-12: Full, high register (D5 melody), 3+4 notes per chord,
  all quarter motion in m.11. Final m.12 settles to root-pos Bb.
============================================================ -->
